Rating: 4
I bought a 2 1/2 lb. bone-in turkey breast and made my own stock by simmering it for an hour with 9 cups water, 1 t. salt, a few peppercorns, and celery, onion, and carrot. This resulted in a generous amount of leftover turkey for sandwiches or whatever in addition to the 2 c. used in this recipe. I then strained the vegetables out and made the rest of the soup mostly as directed, but instead of the farfalle I used about 1 c. orzo. I think the reason some reviewers felt this was tasteless is that the recipe calls for no added salt during cooking, so in addition to the salt I used in the broth, I added 1/2 t. of ground sea salt and 1/4 t. freshly ground pepper when sauteeing the carrots/celery/onion. It is also important to sautee the vegetables at a high temperature, stirring constantly to avoid burning them, to develop a nice rich flavor before adding the broth. The entire family, including teens, loved this soup. A keeper for sure.

Rating: 4
