Rating: 4
I use this recipe frequently, once with turkey left overs and now many times with chicken. My family loves this and its reasonably healthy. I chop all veggies (not together) in a processor. I use 1 fresh lemon ( grated and squeezed) so the flavor is better than that of store bought.. I have never had a problem with a lack of flavor. As I've made this many times, I do use 1/2 the pasta and add 1C of broth; I don't like it too thick. I also heat soup as directed then place spinach in the bowl (not the pot) before adding soup. It wilts perfectly and leaves remaining soup without over-done spinach. This way left overs are still great. Despite adding extra broth this soup has always had great flavor, don't know what the previous reviewer didn't do. but you cant please everyone...

