I liked this a lot in theory but have tweaked it as follows. I substituted store-bought rotisserie chicken for the turkey. I omitted the red pepper. I added two bay leaves to the onions, garlic, celery, and carrots. I deglazed the pan with a cup or two of dry, white wine before adding the chicken broth. I added one 15 oz. can diced tomatoes and a large sprig of fresh thyme with the chicken broth. Other than that I left it alone except for garnishing with a very small drizzle of olive oil and always using parmigiano reggiano. Keep plenty of extra broth on hand for thinning; the pasta absorbs a lot. This is a fantastic alternative to traditional chicken noodle soup. Delicious.

